# How To Push Code to Heroku, follow these steps :

### VirtualEnvironment
1.  Create venv
2.  Create Project
3.  install packages in venv

### Keep Track of the runtime version if Python
4.  create runtime.txt

### Run/Debug Projects 
5.  run project 

### Make it Heroku Servable
6.  install gunicorn
7.  create Procfile

### Gather all Requirements at one place
8.  run "pip freeze > requirements.txt"

### Push to github for version management and ease
9.  Initialise Git Repo
10. Create .gitignore
11. Add venv and __pycache__ and .vscode to gitignore
12. Push to github

### On the Heroku Side
13. Create Heroku Project
14. Add Git Repo to Heroku
15. Watch Build Log

### Finally Run the App
16. Open App
